[Vaccination of 12- to 15-year-old children should provide some protection against MIS-C, which mostly affects children between 1 and 14, with a median age of 9 years. But those children under the age of 12 are still high risk.

"Of all the COVID-19 cases (in France), 58% are infected with the variant B.1.1.7. But in the 0-9 age group, the variant's spread is at 68%."

"Dr. A Somer (Istanbul University Medical Department) noted that there wasn't a definitive explanation as to why children younger than 9 were affected more from COVID-19 and said that it could be explained by their weaker immune system. 'It could also be that they fail to keep social distancing or in wearing masks, because children in this age-group are far more social beings'" (excerpted from https://www.dailysabah.com/life/science/british-covid-19-variant-more-infectious-in-children-data-shows). - Mod.LK]

